* Iron Raptor smiled teasingly at Prowl as the doors of the Ark drew up and soon were opened by her hand, the way she carried her body a bit seductive but just joking around.*

" As a matter of fac..."

* Her sentence was cut short by the blair of a Predacon's voice over the inter-com, it was almost so shocking that she nearly could have fallen backwards!
A Maximal couldn't ever hope to try and cooperate with a Predacon, it had been that way for far to long for things to change now.
Iron Raptor then stopped with her hand on the door and looking blankly at it, not an expression on her face as she pondered what had been said over the communicator.
It would be an extremely bad idea to trust the Predacon's off hand like they wanted, she wasn't even sure if Liono was going to be conned into believing then or not. She knew for a fact that if it was her she would arm the auto guns and have every one of her soldiers armed to the teeth and their weapons almost shoved up the Predacon's noses before she even looked at them. But that was her, Liono was a different story all together.
Iron Raptor then looked back at Prowl with a sigh, obviously she was very tired and needed to sleep more then to repair but this bothered her...very much. The look in her optics when she looked at Prowl told both these things, obviously stressing her a bit.*

" I hope that...we don't...just get a bunch of back stabbing bots...ready to cut our throats at the soonest...oppertunity."

* The last of her words were nothing more then a muffled gasp as she suddenly felt her wounded side spring into a but of a painful spasm. But then she struggled and regained her posture, moving the door asides and moving even more slowly into the base and towards the CR chambers. She just hoped that an all out battle didn't break out while she was repairing, may the Matrix forbid if it did!*
